===========================================================================
									AUTHENTICATION SERVICE README FILE
===========================================================================
This Authentication service will provide you a easy-to-use service for all
your applications and your clients.

===========================================================================
														RUN THE APPLICATION
===========================================================================
Prerequisites : Check line 11 of the s_auth.rb is not commented : enable :sessions

At the root of the project, launch the command:
	$ruby s_auth.rb

The server will run and you can reach it with the url : http://localhost:4567/


===========================================================================
														TEST THE APPLICATION
===========================================================================
1. When the server is launched, launch your favorite web browser at the address:
http://localhost:4567/

2. Now by clicking register, you can add an user.

Indeed, once you have registered an user, you will be redirected to the
user profile in which you can see his used application, his developed
application, create an application or disconnect.

3. When you click on create an application, to test the application exemples,
type in name and url:
	-appli_cliente_1
	-http://localhost:1800

and:
	-appli_cliente_2
	-http://localhost:1801

After creating an application, you will be redirected to the user page
and you could see the developed application in your profile.

4. The service also contains two examples of applications that use the
authentication service (appli_cliente_1.rb, appli_cliente_2.rb).
To start it, at the root of the project, launch the command:
	$ruby appli_cliente_1.rb
  $ruby appli_cliente_2.rb

5. The first client application will run and you can reach it with the url : 
http://localhost:1800/protected
The second client application will run and you can reach it with the url : 
http://localhost:1801/protected

This will required an authentication and after redirect you to the 
protected area of the client application.


===========================================================================
														ORIENTED-RSPEC DEVELOPMENT
===========================================================================
Prerequisites : Comment line 11 of the s_auth.rb : #enable :sessions

You will find my rspec tests in the folder called spec/
For example, to run the s_auth_spec you have to type at the project root:
$ rspec spec/s_auth_spec.rb --format documentation


